cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.ET

This paper is about training deep neural networks for binary communication, which is a topic related to neural networks and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on tasks such as image classification and semantic segmentation, which are related to computer vision, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance-per-watt improvements of low-power and embedded neuromorphic processors, which falls under the sub-category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Finally, the paper also mentions the size and timing of the networks, which are related to machine learning and optimization, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible sub-category.
